abstract: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro on Friday defended his son from accusations of corruption and attacked the Rio de Janeiro state prosecutors leading an investigation of Senator Flavio Bolsonaro's alleged money laundering and misuse of public funds.
snippet: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro on Friday defended his son from accusations of corruption and attacked the Rio de Janeiro state prosecutors leading an investigation of Senator Flavio Bolsonaro's alleged money laundering and misuse of public fun...
lead_paragraph: RIO DE JANEIRO/BRASILIA — Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro on Friday defended his son from accusations of corruption and attacked the Rio de Janeiro state prosecutors leading an investigation of Senator Flavio Bolsonaro's alleged money laundering and misuse of public funds.
headline_main: Brazil's Bolsonaro Defends Son Against Deepening Graft Probe
headline_print_headline: Brazil's Bolsonaro Defends Son Against Deepening Graft Probe

abstract: More than 8 million people have signed up for coverage next year under former President Barack Obama's health care law, the government said Friday,  a sign of continued demand for the program amid persistent uncertainty over its future.
snippet: More than 8 million people have signed up for coverage next year under former President Barack Obama's health care law, the government said Friday,  a sign of continued demand for the program amid persistent uncertainty over its future.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — More than 8 million people have signed up for coverage next year under former President Barack Obama's health care law, the government said Friday, a sign of continued demand for the program amid persistent uncertainty over its future.
headline_main: Obamacare Sign-Ups Steady as Debate Persists Over Its Future
headline_print_headline: Obamacare Sign-Ups Steady as Debate Persists Over Its Future

abstract: An investigation concluded that the Treasury Department’s top spokeswoman did not commit research misconduct, but required extensive revisions.
snippet: An investigation concluded that the Treasury Department’s top spokeswoman did not commit research misconduct, but required extensive revisions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Monica Crowley, the Treasury Department’s assistant secretary for public affairs, committed “localized instances of plagiarism” in her 2000 Ph.D. dissertation, Columbia University found in an investigation that ultimately concluded she did not commit research misconduct.

abstract: Tens of thousands of Algerians protested on Friday, rejecting the election of newly sworn-in President Abdelmadjid Tebboune as their mass movement debates a response to his offer of talks.
snippet: Tens of thousands of Algerians protested on Friday, rejecting the election of newly sworn-in President Abdelmadjid Tebboune as their mass movement debates a response to his offer of talks.
lead_paragraph: ALGIERS — Tens of thousands of Algerians protested on Friday, rejecting the election of newly sworn-in President Abdelmadjid Tebboune as their mass movement debates a response to his offer of talks.
headline_main: Algerians Protest After New President Inaugurated
headline_print_headline: Algerians Protest After New President Inaugurated

abstract: Police in eSwatini arrested the head of the southern African country's largest opposition party and several other politicians and activists in raids on their houses on Friday, their parties said.
snippet: Police in eSwatini arrested the head of the southern African country's largest opposition party and several other politicians and activists in raids on their houses on Friday, their parties said.
lead_paragraph: MBABANE — Police in eSwatini arrested the head of the southern African country's largest opposition party and several other politicians and activists in raids on their houses on Friday, their parties said.
headline_main: eSwatini Opposition Leaders, Activists Targeted in Police Raids
headline_print_headline: eSwatini Opposition Leaders, Activists Targeted in Police Raids

lead_paragraph: CENTERVILLE, Iowa — Minnesota Sen. Amy Klobuchar has argued for weeks that Pete Buttigieg, the mayor of a small Indiana city, doesn't have enough experience to be a serious contender for the Democratic nomination for president. As she heads into a 27-county tour of Iowa, the lead-off caucus state, s he's seeing some payoff for bringing those frustrations fully into public view.
headline_main: Klobuchar Steps Up Hits on Buttigieg With Iowa Vote Looming
headline_print_headline: Klobuchar Steps Up Hits on Buttigieg With Iowa Vote Looming

abstract: At stake is control of the country’s National Assembly, which is controlled by the opposition leader Juan Guaidó, who has accused President Nicolás Maduro of corruption.
snippet: At stake is control of the country’s National Assembly, which is controlled by the opposition leader Juan Guaidó, who has accused President Nicolás Maduro of corruption.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States accused President Nicolás Maduro of Venezuela on Friday of trying to rig a coming election for control of his country’s parliament, either by detaining opposition leaders or bribing lawmakers with up to $500,000 for each vote.

abstract: The Trump administration on Friday said it has finalized a decision to roll back a 2007 rule calling for energy-efficient light bulbs, a move that states including New York and California are challenging in the courts.
snippet: The Trump administration on Friday said it has finalized a decision to roll back a 2007 rule calling for energy-efficient light bulbs, a move that states including New York and California are challenging in the courts.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration on Friday said it has finalized a decision to roll back a 2007 rule calling for energy-efficient light bulbs, a move that states including New York and California are challenging in the courts.
headline_main: U.S. Rolls Back Standards on Energy Saving Light Bulbs
headline_print_headline: U.S. Rolls Back Standards on Energy Saving Light Bulbs

abstract: Washington state Republican lawmakers urged one of their own to resign after a state report found that he engaged in "domestic terrorism" against the United States by participating in armed conflict through the right-wing militia movement.
snippet: Washington state Republican lawmakers urged one of their own to resign after a state report found that he engaged in "domestic terrorism" against the United States by participating in armed conflict through the right-wing militia movement.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Washington state Republican lawmakers urged one of their own to resign after a state report found that he engaged in "domestic terrorism" against the United States by participating in armed conflict through the right-wing militia movement.
headline_main: Washington State Lawmaker Under Pressure to Step Down Over 'Domestic Terrorism'
headline_print_headline: Washington State Lawmaker Under Pressure to Step Down Over 'Domestic Terrorism'
